  <num>46-418</num>
  <heading>Waiver of certain requirements.</heading>
  <text>If a judge of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia determines that public policy or the physical condition of either of the persons applying for a marriage license requires the intended marriage to be celebrated without delay, he may waive the provisions of § 46-409, and a license may be issued without regard to such sections.</text>
